  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Human Multidrug Related Protein 2 (MRP2) excretes several drugs and could therefore modulate
      their elimination. Individual's MRP2 activity is under genetic control. Thus it would be very
      useful to get an easily measurable biomarker reflecting individual's MRP2 activity. We aimed
      to investigate the ratio of urinary coproporphyrins I and III (UCP(I/I+III), known to be
      increased in patients with mutations in MRP2/ABCC2 gene.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
